[src:gaussian-processes-sci/bayesian-optimization] Bayesian optimization is often described through a noiseless, single-objective problem, but the same model-based loop is adapted to several related settings.
[src:gaussian-processes-sci/bayesian-optimization] In noisy Bayesian optimization, evaluations return observations such as $y=f(x)+\varepsilon$ instead of exact values of the latent objective.
